1-4 ur fav n00b zone (i like wfp or gfay)<br>
4-12 or so, orc hill in gfay (if ur de like me it jus sux cus u cant go here but no biggy go to ec and solo ruins or group orcs)<br>
Once you hit 12 head to OOT hehe<br>
12-16 solo sirens (u can pull this off at 8 using the bolt spell glitch, or atleast I could and I was twink) you can take the 2 spawn, 1 spawn, or both and take goblins too depending on how daring you are.<br>
16-20 hit gargoyel island the skeletons are PHs and still give decent exp at his lvl. You will find your the only class that can solo gargs at such low lvl.<br>
20-24 if you need cash and dont mind faction go group for treants. Otherwise aviaks in OOT or LR are good.<br>
24-34 kill the named sisters in OOT on sister island (dock and tree spawn usually) or the dworfs on the same island there is a 1 or 2 spawn. Brutes in WW in the cave to Dalnir are also great till 29.<br>
34-39 if you dont mind faction kill guards in WC. if you do then you might want to try SolB /shrug never did anything but guards at this lvl.<br>
39-44 you have several options at this lvl. Dworfs in BB are good but can be tuff (good till 46). Yetis in DL are good there is a 6 spawn (2 walkers) in one of the caves, they are easy. and for cash dr00ds in WC (ull need to get someone to harmony them to brake spawn and they have faction)<br>
44-49 group or solo in DL. I like mage kiting with fire pet between the ne and se ruins here. (DL can be good exp till 51)<br>
49-55 your fire pet will rip through SF's in OOT and he Wizards in neriak 3rd gate are good too (they do not have faction hit so you fellow DEs can kill them if you want)<br>
After 55 you're on your own cus I dont know yet. Although I hear dino in oot can be good exp. but I dont know if mages can take at 55, necros can...<br>
<br>
Thats about it, for this I used air pet all the way, and I have the focuses as well. Many of these camps require (or are MUCH easyer with highest pet. For mage kiting obviously use fire pet. (Earth for root/nuke I dont like, the pet takes 20% more dmg because of roots and you waste mana)<br>
<br>
These are jus my opinions, hope it does you some good. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uultimica.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ultimica</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0> at: 2/22/02 8:06:40 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uquinean.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quinean</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#333333>(2/27/02 8:39:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=347.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Where to Solo 1-55</span><hr size=1> This is a great guide.<br>
<br>
I did gargs in oot 23-24. Decent xp and lots of fun. Live for those double eye drops.<br>
<br>
I did loio 25-29, camped on the south shore, pulled from the hills just south of that.<br>
<br>
Golras from 30-34. Safe, boring, steady xp. Loot not so good.<br>
<br>
Thurgy mines from 35-39. Great fun. Giant heads from goo's can net you up to 100p each, don't settle for less than 50.<br>
<br>
Dawnshroud from 40 to 45 (I'm 45 now). Large zelniaks until 44, then they light out for the most part. Pick on the wolves then, or partner/group and do hoppers.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
